03:16.784 --> 03:18.546
I can just see that thief responded,

03:19.426 --> 03:26.513
You know that man in the cross, his name is Jesus, he told me that he'll meet me here today.

03:30.758 --> 03:31.218
Amazing.

03:33.200 --> 03:39.046
The only reason why that thief was in heaven was because of the power of the cross.

03:40.728 --> 03:46.514
And that's where we're gonna be talking about today, the message and the power of the cross.

03:48.034 --> 03:49.556
What is the message of the cross?

03:50.617 --> 03:53.160
You know, I'm gonna give it to you in simple terms.

03:53.600 --> 03:55.923
It's a big, I love you from God.

03:58.066 --> 03:59.387
Christ died for sinners.

04:00.008 --> 04:01.870
He died for people who messed up.

04:03.091 --> 04:05.815
He did not die because he was forced upon him.

04:07.076 --> 04:10.740
It was a choice, a choice done in love.

04:11.721 --> 04:15.666
Let's go to our first text, Romans 5, 8.

04:18.114 --> 04:21.459
But God demonstrates his own love for us in this.

04:22.561 --> 04:26.387
While we were still sinners, Christ died for us.

04:27.929 --> 04:29.352
See, he didn't just say, I love you.

04:30.073 --> 04:30.794
I love you, Alan.

04:31.896 --> 04:33.298
No, he acted.

04:33.318 --> 04:35.401
He put actions behind those words.

04:39.067 --> 04:46.098
Folks, I'm not here this morning to tell you something you don't already know, but rather that we would remind each other

04:46.338 --> 04:49.001
of that which we must never, ever forget.

04:51.765 --> 04:55.890
The world as we know it has tried to lessen the meaning of the cross.

04:57.152 --> 04:59.915
Governments have attempted to overrule its power.

05:00.956 --> 05:02.678
Most religions have rejected it.

05:05.081 --> 05:13.772
Schools have kicked it out of their classrooms, and even worse, most contemporary churches are watering it down.

05:14.493 --> 05:15.154
Why?

05:15.682 --> 05:18.145
because it's not popular anymore.

05:19.567 --> 05:22.351
It's old news, and it happened a very long time ago.

05:25.615 --> 05:26.396
Let me tell you this.

05:26.536 --> 05:30.602
It might be old, but it's still the best news ever.

05:32.224 --> 05:40.816
No event, none, in the history of mankind can come close to its power and impact and humanity in everyone's life.

05:42.998 --> 05:45.682
This is what was preached when I first came here.

05:46.018 --> 05:54.670
37 years ago in the San Ramon Valley Bible Church, and that same message is still and will still be preached as long as this church stands.

05:56.773 --> 06:01.920
The world has changed and it will keep on changing, but the message of the cross won't.

06:03.542 --> 06:05.565
Our preaching style might change.

06:06.847 --> 06:07.828
Preachers will get old.

06:07.848 --> 06:08.529
What am I talking about?

06:08.629 --> 06:15.218
I am old, but the message of the cross will never, ever lose its power.

06:16.002 --> 06:20.570
It will be as powerful and effected as it was 2000 years ago.

06:23.094 --> 06:24.837
I only have two points today.

06:25.438 --> 06:28.382
First is our attitude toward the cross.

06:30.666 --> 06:33.791
Let's read 1 Corinthians 1 17.

06:36.696 --> 06:42.706
For Christ, this is Paul talking, for Christ did not send me to baptize, but to preach the gospel.

06:43.362 --> 06:48.430
not with wisdom and eloquence lest the cross of Christ be emptied of its power."

06:49.131 --> 06:49.551
Here we go.

06:49.992 --> 06:59.046
For the message of the cross is foolishness to those who are perishing, but to us who are being saved, it is the power of God.

07:02.431 --> 07:09.842
To those who do not have faith in God, the idea of a crucified Savior can seem foolish.

07:11.042 --> 07:13.225
They see the cross as a symbol of weakness.

07:14.807 --> 07:24.860
To many in the world, the idea that a God would choose to die, a humiliating and painful death for the sake of humanity might seem absurd.

07:24.900 --> 07:30.428
To crucify an innocent man sounds crazy.

07:34.654 --> 07:41.042
The cross shows us the seriousness of our sins and symbolizes the severity

07:41.122 --> 07:42.003
of our weakness.

07:43.245 --> 07:51.316
They forget that the cross was meant for our sins, that those nails, those nails were supposed to go through our hands.

07:52.978 --> 07:57.344
But these days we think our sins just deserve a slap on the wrist.

07:59.607 --> 08:04.934
Bible says that the wages of sin, the price of sin, is death.

08:05.655 --> 08:06.296
I didn't say that.

08:06.696 --> 08:07.858
That's what the word says.

08:09.026 --> 08:15.194
They don't get it because they're thinking in worldly wisdom, as stated in the verses we just read.

08:16.155 --> 08:25.728
The message of the cross demands that we forsake all reliance on any human wisdom, any human power, and any human resource.

08:27.931 --> 08:34.980
You see, friends, high human intellect or education can sometimes get in the way of a relationship to God.

08:35.981 --> 08:36.562
Hold on.

08:36.930 --> 08:39.914
Don't get the idea that God is against education, no?

08:40.554 --> 08:41.155
I didn't say that.

08:41.456 --> 08:44.920
And God is against intellectual excellence, no.

08:46.221 --> 08:50.407
But don't ever think that that is going to be your bridge to God.

08:51.308 --> 08:54.632
There's only one way to God, and that's through His Son, Jesus Christ.

08:57.976 --> 09:01.540
But to us who are being saved, it is the power of God.

09:03.583 --> 09:06.226
Folks, I just hope that today you can regain some

09:07.010 --> 09:09.893
appreciations for these words again.

09:09.933 --> 09:18.743
Maybe clear away some of those religious cobwebs that have been in your mind and try to comprehend the overwhelming meaning of this verse.

09:20.465 --> 09:27.732
That we can be saved because a man died in agonizing, humiliating, torturous death.

09:29.394 --> 09:36.722
Even though it's regarded as foolish by some, to those who trust in it, to those who are being saved, it is the power

09:37.058 --> 09:37.539
of God.

09:39.462 --> 09:47.794
It's not saying that the message of the cross talks about the power of God or it teaches about the power of God.

09:48.035 --> 09:52.522
He says that the message of the cross is the power of God.

09:54.164 --> 09:59.813
There is an amazing power in the preaching of the true gospel when it is received with faith.

10:01.035 --> 10:05.842
The hearing and the trusting of the true gospel will bring the power of God

10:06.146 --> 10:07.447
into your lap, into mine.

10:11.111 --> 10:15.876
Folks, preaching about the disciples is not the gospel.

10:17.317 --> 10:21.241
Preaching a high moral standard is not the gospel.

10:22.042 --> 10:25.025
Preaching about good works is not the gospel.

10:25.705 --> 10:29.229
The message of the cross is the gospel.

10:30.930 --> 10:33.573
Without the cross, none of us would be here.

10:34.334 --> 10:34.674
None.

10:37.602 --> 10:39.464
There would be no good news to preach.

10:39.544 --> 10:40.285
I wouldn't be up here.

10:40.465 --> 10:41.406
What would I talk about?

10:43.449 --> 10:49.275
This gathering of saints, the encouraging one another, the serving one another, it would not simply exist.

10:51.037 --> 10:54.481
We are only here because of what he did at the cross.

10:55.843 --> 11:03.492
That is the theme we have every Sunday morning to honor and thank him for paying our sin debt on cavalry.

11:03.972 --> 11:05.554
Remember how big that bill was?

11:07.042 --> 11:07.783
It's now stamped.

11:08.343 --> 11:10.726
It says, paid in his blood, with his blood.

11:13.168 --> 11:16.011
For us believers, this message is not simply a story.

11:16.551 --> 11:21.296
No, it is the very foundation of our faith and the source of our salvation.

11:22.537 --> 11:28.143
We see the cross as the ultimate expression of God's love and power.

11:31.326 --> 11:35.250
My second point, our response to the message of the cross

11:36.610 --> 11:37.791
Let's read this passage.

11:38.392 --> 11:40.474
Luke 23, 32 to 43.

11:41.935 --> 11:43.096
It's about the thief on the cross.

11:46.340 --> 11:51.945
Two other men, both criminals, were also led out with him to be executed.

11:52.826 --> 11:57.711
When they came to the place called the skull, they crucified him there along with the criminals.

11:58.852 --> 12:01.455
One on his right and the other on his left.

12:03.016 --> 12:04.818
Jesus said, Father, forgive them.

12:05.570 --> 12:07.612
for they do not know what they are doing."

12:08.713 --> 12:09.494
I don't know about that.

12:09.614 --> 12:11.416
I thought people knew what they were doing.

12:13.319 --> 12:15.921
And they divided up his clothes by casting lots.

12:16.302 --> 12:19.686
The people stood watching and the rulers even sneered at him.

12:20.146 --> 12:25.432
They said, he saved others, let him save himself if he is God's Messiah, the chosen one.

12:27.354 --> 12:29.356
The soldiers also came up and mocked him.

12:29.757 --> 12:34.642
They offered him, wine vinegar and said, if you are the king of the Jews, save yourself.

12:36.834 --> 12:40.298
There was a written notice above him, which read, this is the king of the Jews.

12:42.400 --> 12:42.901
Here we go.

12:44.563 --> 12:47.866
One of the criminals who hung there hurled insults at him.

12:49.108 --> 12:50.049
Aren't you the Messiah?

12:50.069 --> 12:52.151
Save yourself and us.

12:53.433 --> 12:55.115
But the other criminal rebuked him.

12:56.476 --> 12:57.417
Don't you fear God?

12:57.437 --> 13:05.106
He said, since you are under the same sentence, we are punished justly.

13:05.858 --> 13:08.641
For we are getting what our deeds deserve.

13:09.902 --> 13:11.644
But this man has done nothing wrong.

13:13.066 --> 13:16.169
Then he said, Jesus, remember me when you come into your kingdom?

13:17.931 --> 13:18.912
Jesus answered him.

13:23.376 --> 13:27.721
Truly, I tell you, today you will be with me in paradise.

13:30.344 --> 13:32.466
I don't know how many times I've read this verse.

13:33.410 --> 13:35.773
but it still gives me goosebumps every time I read it.

13:39.237 --> 13:43.082
Crucifixion by the Romans was we all know a death sentence.

13:43.883 --> 13:48.168
It was designed specifically to be the most excruciating way to die.

13:49.369 --> 13:56.478
It was nailing the victim to the cross by their wrist and by their feet, and the victim would not die from the nails through their flesh.

13:57.899 --> 13:59.662
But they would die from suffocating.

14:00.903 --> 14:03.346
In fact, the way that they were positioned on the cross

14:04.514 --> 14:06.337
made it so difficult to breathe.

14:07.158 --> 14:09.782
So they had to push up with their feet to get some relief.

14:11.004 --> 14:16.372
The arms would carry so much of the weight that it would eventually dislocate their shoulders.

14:18.535 --> 14:22.160
Because of this, someone at the cross would die very slowly and painfully.

14:22.901 --> 14:25.285
And sometimes it would take hours or even days.

14:28.890 --> 14:34.098
This type of death was generally reserved for people who were

14:34.498 --> 14:36.321
the empires most wanted.

14:38.504 --> 14:41.428
Let's look at the first criminal, the rebellious one.

14:42.269 --> 14:46.094
But note, first note, that both thieves had the same death sentence.

14:49.178 --> 14:54.626
According to the Roman authorities, neither one of them were fit to live on this earth another day.

14:56.008 --> 15:03.538
The so-called good thief lived his entire life in sin, just as the so-called bad one did.

15:04.482 --> 15:06.144
There was no behavioral differences.

15:07.406 --> 15:10.310
Very bad people who didn't deserve jail time but death.

15:11.852 --> 15:18.280
Both had the same opportunity with Jesus and yet we see a contrast between them.

15:20.103 --> 15:25.630
One saw it as foolishness and the other as a power to save.

15:28.414 --> 15:29.415
Aren't you the Messiah?

15:30.757 --> 15:31.698
Save yourself.

15:32.354 --> 15:37.080
That's what the religious leaders and the crowd yelled initially as they taunted Jesus.

15:38.882 --> 15:39.423
And guess what?

15:39.503 --> 15:43.768
This rebellious thief eventually joined with the crowd.

15:47.053 --> 15:48.274
Isn't that what we see today?

15:50.337 --> 15:56.665
Let me join in what's popular when even though it's not right.

15:59.228 --> 16:00.850
I don't want to go against the crowd.

16:02.338 --> 16:12.313
Instead of defending Christ, this thief seemed to have sealed his heart with bitterness and disdain despite sharing the same painful faith as his companion.

16:13.235 --> 16:20.686
He chose to follow a path of mockery and defiance, not only towards his own situation, but also towards Jesus.

16:23.070 --> 16:26.856
Instead of seeking redemption, he decided to ridicule.

16:28.699 --> 16:30.962
Folks, this man represents pride

16:32.578 --> 16:33.419
at its finest.

16:35.281 --> 16:46.913
This man represents those who even in the face of pure manifestation of love and grace choose to close themselves off and reject it.

16:48.675 --> 16:56.523
His choice highlights the deep importance of our personal decisions and how we respond to opportunities for salvation.

16:58.505 --> 16:59.666
Save yourself and us.

17:00.642 --> 17:03.607
If you have the power to get us both out of here, prove it, do it.

17:05.249 --> 17:07.773
Maybe then I can believe you, maybe.

17:09.696 --> 17:12.961
But I need to get off this cross so I can go on living my life again.

17:14.704 --> 17:18.510
Basically he's telling the Lord, Lord, I want to go back to my sinful life.

17:21.294 --> 17:25.981
These thief wanted to get saved from death, but he wanted it on his terms.

17:27.524 --> 17:29.106
He wanted to be rescued.

17:30.658 --> 17:31.879
But it had to be his way.

17:33.120 --> 17:34.482
That's not how it works, folks.

17:36.443 --> 17:37.184
A quick story.

