20:08.652 --> 20:12.117
Now even though I had good intentions, it didn't matter.

20:14.260 --> 20:15.262
I'm the rescuer.

20:16.504 --> 20:17.866
God is doing the rescuing.

20:22.172 --> 20:23.314
Let's look at the other thief.

20:26.946 --> 20:35.679
You'll find that in both the book of Matthew and Mark, both thieves were said to have been ridiculing Jesus at the beginning.

20:37.602 --> 20:50.582
According to the detailed account in the book of Luke, he had more details, during the last hours of suffering, one thief noticed that indeed something extremely unusual was taking place.

20:52.425 --> 20:55.730
The centurion at the foot of the cross made the same observation

20:56.290 --> 20:59.013
when he remarked, surely this is the Son of God.

21:01.215 --> 21:11.345
This thief understood that the one dying on the middle of the cross was not dying for any crimes he had committed, but he was dying for the sins of others.

21:13.548 --> 21:17.191
There are three things that you need to notice from the last words of this thief.

21:18.212 --> 21:21.516
First, he recognizes just condemnation.

21:22.677 --> 21:23.858
In his final moments,

21:24.994 --> 21:31.563
He said, we are punished justly for we receive the due reward of our deeds.

21:33.245 --> 21:36.529
So he understood that he deserved to be in that position.

21:40.254 --> 21:52.370
You know, we live in a day and age where oftentimes people look at those who are suffering and they think that maybe it's an act of God or it's just bad luck or it's faith.

21:52.578 --> 21:56.402
or whatever, but this guy, even in his last moments, got it right.

21:58.164 --> 22:01.468
He said, no, we deserve this.

22:01.828 --> 22:02.569
I deserve this.

22:04.391 --> 22:10.598
We have done things that we should have not done, and we are receiving the consequences of our actions.

22:12.020 --> 22:18.887
He basically owned his mistakes and did not blame anyone or anything else.

22:20.129 --> 22:21.170
This is all on me.

22:22.946 --> 22:29.415
The second thing that we need to notice from the last words of this thief is that he acknowledged the truth about Jesus.

22:31.218 --> 22:36.445
Listen, here's what he says, but this man has done nothing wrong.

22:38.728 --> 22:42.093
He saw an innocent man was being killed.

22:43.054 --> 22:46.579
He watched Jesus stay quiet as they continued to torture him.

22:48.682 --> 22:51.506
He heard him utter the words, father, forgive them.

22:52.514 --> 22:54.577
For they do not know what they are doing.

22:54.637 --> 22:57.922
He realized that Jesus is more than just a man.

22:59.945 --> 23:06.254
And then finally, with his last words, his thief made a very, very simple request.

23:09.179 --> 23:10.781
He didn't try to bargain with Jesus.

23:10.821 --> 23:12.123
He didn't try to negotiate.

23:14.146 --> 23:15.508
He had nothing to offer him.

23:17.431 --> 23:20.395
He simply said, remember me.

23:21.677 --> 23:22.258
That's it.

23:23.362 --> 23:29.370
He couldn't even ask those words, forgive me, Lord, because he knew he didn't deserve it.

23:30.912 --> 23:33.496
But thank God Jesus knew his heart.

23:37.221 --> 23:38.262
And what did Jesus do?

23:44.210 --> 23:52.882
With a broken jaw, busted mouth, and difficulty breathing, Jesus turned his bloody head

23:54.722 --> 24:08.857
and mustered up what strength he had left, and said with no hesitation or no delay, truly I tell you today, you will be with me in paradise."

24:12.582 --> 24:14.384
You didn't say, let me think about it.

24:16.766 --> 24:17.687
You didn't say, you know what?

24:17.707 --> 24:19.009
You should see a priest first.

24:21.331 --> 24:23.954
The thief was already in the presence of the high priest.

24:24.450 --> 24:26.852
the highest you could ever ask for.

24:28.134 --> 24:31.537
Jesus didn't say, say a series of prayers and hope for the best.

24:33.899 --> 24:36.502
He didn't say, you need to get your life together first.

24:37.923 --> 24:41.887
No, he granted his request right there on the spot.

24:44.530 --> 24:48.474
And I love that Jesus didn't give him what he wanted, but gave him what he needed.

24:50.796 --> 24:52.658
The thief just wanted remembrance.

24:53.762 --> 24:55.123
God gave him redemption.

24:57.326 --> 25:02.051
Folks, that's what we call amazing grace.

25:04.253 --> 25:04.874
Ken was right.

25:06.015 --> 25:09.359
That word amazing is only reserved for God's grace.

25:12.262 --> 25:14.865
Anyone here came to Christ with his life cleaned up?

25:16.547 --> 25:17.808
Did you have it all together?

25:17.848 --> 25:19.350
No.

25:21.312 --> 25:22.994
We were all a hot mess.

25:23.074 --> 25:29.404
I was a hot mess, broken, hopeless, and nothing good to offer.

25:31.368 --> 25:33.631
But that's the way God wants us.

25:34.693 --> 25:37.898
That's the way this thief came to Jesus.

25:40.122 --> 25:43.948
Friend, salvation is a gift, not a reward.

25:45.070 --> 25:47.634
It was never meant for us to earn it.

25:52.546 --> 25:56.531
In my conclusion, this criminal made the right choice for once in his life.

25:58.854 --> 26:03.260
He didn't escape death that day, but he sure escaped eternity in damnation.

26:05.883 --> 26:10.969
This criminal entered heaven only because of the power of the cross.

26:13.312 --> 26:16.416
The message of the cross gave him power to be saved.

26:18.299 --> 26:20.882
And friend, that's the same message I offer.

26:21.282 --> 26:23.966
to the person who hasn't made that choice today.

26:28.112 --> 26:35.842
And once you choose Jesus as your Lord and Savior, you can claim that same promise.

26:35.942 --> 26:42.732
Those same words of promise He gave that criminal, you will be with me in paradise.

26:43.153 --> 26:43.473
Amen?

26:44.815 --> 26:45.416
Let's close.

26:46.157 --> 26:47.058
Heavenly Father,

26:49.890 --> 26:53.655
We thank you that the story of this criminal is in the Word.

26:53.695 --> 27:03.168
It's very encouraging to most of us because Lord, none of us came with life altogether.

27:03.809 --> 27:04.530
We were a mess.

27:05.431 --> 27:08.535
Thank you that it was all about you.

27:09.056 --> 27:12.200
It was your work, not mine, not any of us.

27:13.201 --> 27:14.182
And so we're thankful.

27:15.744 --> 27:19.890
Please Lord, if there's anyone here who has not committed their lives to you,

27:20.034 --> 27:22.421
today be the day of their salvation.

27:24.206 --> 27:31.266
Lord, thank you for this time, thank you for your word, and thank you for the power it gives us.

27:31.587 --> 27:32.690
In Jesus' name, amen.

